<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h3><a name="Overview_of_Minimal_System_for_T"></a> Overview of Minimal System for Training Session </h3>
The ideal minimal preparation for benefitting from the Tier-3 training session
is two PC's installed with SL4, and no Firewalls. You then install a batch system
that allows you to use PC 1 to submit a job to PC 2. In addition, you export
the filesystem of PC 1 to PC 2.
<p />
A minimal system like this will allow you to participate in all the exercises at the
Tier-3 training session.
<p />
<h3><a name="Detailed_Specifications_of_a_Pro"></a> Detailed Specifications of a Production Tier-3 </h3>
<p /> <ul>
<li> <a href="/bin/view/Education/RecommendedHardware" class="twikiLink">RecommendedHardware</a> (Steve)
</li> <li> <a href="/bin/view/Trash/ReleaseDocumentationOperatingSystems" class="twikiLink">Operating System</a> (Jorge)
</li> <li> <a href="/bin/view/Education/NetworkingConstraints" class="twikiLink">NetworkingConstraints</a> (Terrence)
</li> <li> Batch systems (Burt will query T3s and see what they want to run) <ul>
<li> <a href="/bin/view/Education/CondorPrereq" class="twikiLink">CondorPrereq</a> (Steve)
</li> <li> <a href="/bin/view/Education/PbsSetup" class="twikiLink">PbsSetup</a> (Craig)
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> <a href="/bin/view/Education/GridCertificates" class="twikiLink">Grid Certificates</a> Trash/Tier3 Administrators need to have a personal certificate before the OSG Trash/Tier3 Workshop (Jorge)
</li></ul> 
